        <h1>General Rules:</h1>
      <font color="black"> <ol>
           <li>Every students on the rolls of the college shall abide by the rules of the College framed from time to time, and shall strictly obey all the directives issued. Students are advised to read the College Notice Board daily.</li>
           <li>If a student, during his stay in the College, is considered undesirable for any reason - his/her name will be strucked off College rolls by the Principal whose orders are final in this connection. The Principal has right of removing the name of a student from the rolls of the College even without  assigning any reason.</li>
           <li>The authority of the College extend over all the Students on this roll in all places and in all times.</li>
           <li>All students must keep thier identity card with them in the College as well as outside the College. This is a must and the defaulters are liable to be fined heavily.</li>
         </ol></font>
          <h1>Leave Rules:</h1>
        <font color="black">  <ol>
              <li>Leave rule should be applied for and got sanctioned in advance except in emergencies when it should be applied for on the day the student resumes studies at the college.</li>
              <li>An application for leave up to four days should be presented personally to the tuitor.When leave is granted the application should be handed over in the office to be filled. the student should keep with him for record the counterfoil duly signed by the clerk incharge . In exceptional cases, application  may be sent by post under registered cover by name to the Principal.</li>
              <li>No leave can granted for a indefinte period. Leave for period of five or more days should be applied for to the Principal personally.</li>
              <li>In case of long illness,the application must be accompanied by a certificate from the College Medical Officer.</li>
          </ol></font>
        
       
         
       
